<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Efforts To Arrange Weizman-al-Shar' Meeting Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Efforts To Arrange Weizman-al-Shar' Meeting Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0805085494 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 8 May 94 p 
17 </F>

<F P=103> TA0805085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There are efforts to arrange a meeting between 
President 'Ezer Weizman and Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq 
al-Shar', both of whom are due to arrive in South Africa today 
to attend Nelson Mandela's inauguration ceremony as president. 
  The Syrians have shown interest in a meeting, but have not 
made any commitment. President Weizman, who leaves for 
Johannesburg this morning by Air Force plane, will meet with a 
number of political figures, including PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat, 
Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto, U.S. Vice President Al 
Gore, and perhaps Jordan's King Husayn, during his visit. 

</TEXT>

