<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knesset Resolution Affirms Jerusalem United Forever </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Knesset Resolution Affirms Jerusalem United Forever </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1005045694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0400 GMT 10 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1005045694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Most Knesset factions voted last night in favor of 
a resolution stating that Jerusalem will forever remain a united 
city under Israeli sovereignty. The Knesset asserts that Israel 
will prevent any attempt to impair the city's status and 
territorial integrity. Jerusalem and its environs are not a 
political or a security issue but the very soul of the Jewish 
people, the Knesset resolution affirms. The resolution was 
initiated by Likud Chairman Binyamin Netanyahu, and Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin endorsed it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

