  [Text] Israel and Morocco are holding contacts over the 
possibility of establishing mutual bureaus of interests. This 
was reported by our political correspondent Shlomo Raz. The 
prime minister's office denies that Yitzhaq Rabin plans to 
travel to Morocco. The prime minister and the foreign minister 
had planned to leave for Morocco immediately after the signing 
of the Israeli- Palestinian agreement in Cairo on 4 May, but the 
visit was canceled at the last moment. It now appears that only 
Mr. Peres will visit Morocco. 

