<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Morocco's King Hassan has urged Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin to pursue the peace process and expressed his 
belief that Israelis and Palestinians can coexist and create a 
new Middle East. These remarks are included in a message sent by 
the king to the prime minister via Knesset Member Rafi Edri, who 
visited Morocco last weekend. 
  Our correspondent Yo'el Nir reports that Moroccan and 
Israeli 
representatives are currently discussing the establishment of 
economic representations in Jerusalem and Rabat, the opening of 
direct aviation routes, and the establishment of telephone and 
postal services between the two countries. 

