<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Interior Ministry has 
denied press reports today that demonstrations have taken place 
in Beirut and elsewhere. The source said that what happened is 
that several popular delegations flocked to the residence of 
Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri to voice their support. 
  The ministry has issued no permit for demonstrations, in 
accordance with a Cabinet decision. 
  Interior Minister Bisharah Mirhij was contacted by Chamber 
Speaker Nabih Birri this morning. They assessed the political 
situation in light of the critical stage through which the 
country is passing. Minister Mirhij affirmed to Speaker Birri 
his commitment to the mainstays of the democratic parliamentary 
system. 

