<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] More than 11,000 basijis [volunteer forces] of Ilam 
Province have enrolled at basij resistance centers and bases and 
are ready to be dispatched to Bosnia-Herzegovina. This follows 
the guidelines issued by the exalted leader of the Islamic 
revolution on all-round support for the Muslims of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The commander of the Islamic Revolution 
Guards for Ilam district said today: If the political obstacles 
to the dispatching of volunteers are removed, and we dispatch 
the first group of volunteers to Bosnia-Herzegovina, the number 
of enrolling volunteers is expected to increase manyfold. He 
added: The enrollment of volunteers in Ilam Province is still 
continuing in urban and rural areas and in offices. 

