<H3> <TI>   UNHCR To Fund Homes for Iraqi Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNHCR To Fund Homes for Iraqi Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705211294 Tehran IRNA in English 2044 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0705211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ahvaz, Khuzestan Prov., May 7, IRNA -- United 
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) is to finance 
installation of 400 pre-fab residential units in a refugee camp 
near Shushtar in this southern province. 
  Head of UNHCR office in Tehran Pierre Jean Bur said that 
pre-fab residential units would begin soon at the Mohsen 
Bani-Najjar refugee camp near Shushtar. He gave no exact date 
for the start of the project. 
  He said the project will be implemented in cooperation with 
the UNHCR office based in Tehran and the foreign national 
section of the Khuzestan Governorate-General. 
  Some 2,400 Iraqi refugees who have fled to Iran are now 
residing in the camp. 

</TEXT>

