<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Official Discusses Export Figures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Official Discusses Export Figures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905103994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The annual export share of the industrial sector, 
affiliated to the Industries Ministry, was 42 percent of the 
country's total industrial exports figure in the year 1372 
[Iranian year ending 20 March 1994]. 
  While announcing this, the industrial and production affairs 
deputy of the Industries Ministry said today in an exclusive 
interview with our correspondent: The country's industrial 
exports figures increased from 60 million dollars in the year 
1368 to 440 million dollars in the year 1372. Thanks to the 
growing trend of exports, it is forecast that the figure will 
increase to 500 million dollars in the current year. 
  He added: A stable rate of foreign currency, precise 
planning 
of industrial projects, and stability of the country's economic 
policy are very effective factors in oiling the wheels of the 
country's industry. He further stressed that the foreign 
currency earned from the non-oil exports fully meets the demands 
of the industrial sector for hard currency. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

