<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Twenty-Two State Firms Ready for Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Twenty-Two State Firms Ready for Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705190294 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0705190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Twenty-two large industrial and production companies 
under the supervision of the Organization for the Development 
and Modernization of Iranian Industries [OEMII] will be 
transferred to the private sector. 
  In a statement published this afternoon, OEMII, an 
affiliation of the Ministry of Heavy Industries, said: In 
accordance with government economic policy, shares in the 22 
companies will be transferred through Tehran's stock exchange or 
auction. 
  Companies whose shares are totally ready for transfer to the 
private sector are active in the production of machines, light 
and heavy vehicles, engines, as well as engineering and 
road-construction machinery. 

</TEXT>

