<DATE1>  7 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank, Belgium Agree To Reschedule Debt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank, Belgium Agree To Reschedule Debt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705065494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0705065494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Republic of Iran and Belgium have 
reached an agreement for the repayment of Iran's debts. This 
agreement was signed by a delegation of the Central Bank of Iran 
and officials from the Belgian Government's insurance institute. 
It includes all Iranian importers' debts which expired by April 
1994 as well as all credit documents for the current year. 
  The initial grace period is 26 months for the agreement and 
the repayment time is four years. In addition to all insured 
dealings, it was agreed all of the noninsured credits will also 
be reimbursed in accordance with these arrangements by banks and 
retailers, as well as the Central Bank of Iran. The sum 
envisaged under this agreement is approximately $200 million. 

</TEXT>

