<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Support Only for Journals Following `Islamic System' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Support Only for Journals Following `Islamic System' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0705211994 Tehran IRNA in English 2100 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0705211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, May 7, IRNA -- According to an official of 
the Ministry of Guidance only the journals that follow the 
strategy of the Islamic system will be supported. 
  The managing director for the domestic press section of 
Culture and Islamic Guidance Ministry Mojtaba Hamedani told IRNA 
here Friday that the press should take into consideration 
objectives of the system, press duties, existing realities and 
the demands of the majority of the people if they claimed they 
were concerned over the cultural growth of the country. 
  "The press and publications acting in accordance with the 
law 
will be supported," Hamedani said. He added that criticism and 
discussing practical strategies to solve the problems was the 
main raison d'etre of the press. 
  He also added that there would be some facilities in the 
future for the press such as a press house, press club and other 
facilities for journalists. 

</TEXT>

