<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Team To Travel to Sanaa via Saudi Arabia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Team To Travel to Sanaa via Saudi Arabia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1005094894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0925 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1005094894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 10 May (MENA)--The Arab League Secretariat 
General has gained Saudi Arabia's approval to receive the Arab 
League delegation that will travel to Saudi territory and from 
there to Yemen overland on a new mediation mission to stop the 
fighting in Yemen. 
  The delegation, led by Major General Bayraqdar, assistant 
Arab League secretary general for military affairs, will leave 
Cairo Airport for Jeddah and from there travel overland to Sanaa 
across the Saudi border. 
  Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has 
asked the delegation to travel to Yemen and meet Yemeni leaders 
in an effort to stop the fighting, resolve the differences, and 
replace the guns with dialogue. 
  In a telephone contact with Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid, Yemeni 
Foreign 
Minister Muhammad Salim Basindwah agreed to guarantee the 
delegation's arrival in Sanaa. 

</TEXT>

