<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri has said: Our aim is 
to preserve the country. What we are seeking through our stance 
is the best interests of the people. 
  Addressing large public delegations that flocked to his 
residence from various areas in Lebanon today, he said: Our 
assets are the good people of this country. The country has had 
enough of 17 years of war. The country has been hijacked for 17 
years, and now is the time for our good people to govern, and 
you represent these good people. There are some who have paid 
the war bill and we will not allow anyone to make you pay the 
peace bill. 
  Al-Hariri made these remarks when he received public figures 
and delegations that visited Quraytim Palace to show support and 
solidarity with the prime minister. 
  At 1900 today al-Hariri received Ministers Bisharah Mirhij, 
'Umar Misqawi, Elie Hubayqah, Hagop Demerdjian, 'Adil Qirtas, 
Muhammad Ghaziri, and As'ad Rizq and Deputies Wajih al-Ba'arini, 
