<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zayid Briefed by Yemen's Salih on Events </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zayid Briefed by Yemen's Salih on Events </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005105494 Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network in 
Arabic 0930 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Abu Dhabi United Arab Emirates Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The president, His Highness Shaykh Zayid Bin-Sultan 
Al Nuhayyan, last night received a telephone call from President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih of the sisterly Republic of Yemen. The 
Yemeni president briefed President Zayid on the latest Yemeni 
developments. 
  Shaykh Zayid asked the Yemeni brothers to resolve their 
differences through reason, logic, and dialogue to serve Yemen 
and the Yemeni people. 
  President Zayid expressed his deep concern over the 
continued 
fighting in Yemen and appealed to all sides to stop fighting 
immediately to end the bloodshed and take the course of dialogue 
and understanding in preparation for resuming good offices and 
mediations to resolve differences and place the interests of 
Yemen and its people above all other considerations. 
  During the telephone conversation, the president said that 
he 
was confident that the Yemeni leaders and figures would be able 
to solve their differences and effect a brotherly reconciliation 
instead of shedding blood, killing, and wasting resources, 
something which saddens every Arab and Muslim. Yemen and its 
people are dear to us and we harbor great love for them. His 
highness said: We appeal to you to fear God in dealing with 
Yemen and its people and to resort to reason instead of arms. 
  His highness warned against aggravating the fighting and the 
resulting inability to control the situation and held the Yemeni 
leaders responsible. He said: We must give advice and do 
whatever we can to steer Yemen away from this painful fate. 
  His highness has been in constant contact with the leaders 
of 
fraternal Yemen for the past several days within his highness' 
endeavors to follow Yemeni developments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

