<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    North Yemen Offers `Immediate Cease-Fire' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1105073194 Paris AFP in English 0724 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1105073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, May 11 (AFP) -- Northern Yemeni leaders 
offered an immediate ceasefire in the civil war on Wednesday if 
their southern rivals agreed to accept President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih's government, a Yemeni envoy said. 
  Salih and his followers have ousted Vice-President 'Ali 
Salim 
al- Bid and other prominent southerners from the government 
since fighting broke out last week, accusing them of wanting 
secession. 
  Planning Minister 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, an envoy of 
Salih, 
said that the "political leadership in Sanaa is ready to accept 
an immediate ceasefire, on condition that they (the southerners) 
respect the constitution." 

</TEXT>

