<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on Events in Yemen; Casualty Tolls Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Civil War Casualty Toll </H4>

<F P=102> NC1105075394 Cairo MENA in English 0730 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1105075394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, May 11 (MENA) -- The number of people killed 
since war erupted in Yemen has reached 119, eight of them 
Somalis, while the wounded reached 489. 
  Director of Military Hospital and Health Service here 
Muhammad Naji told MENA correspondent today that out of those 
casualties 79 military officers were killed and 299 were 
wounded. The rest are civilians and foreigners. 
  The number of Somalis wounded in the Yemen civil war has 
reached 39, director of health services said. There are several 
thousand Somalis living here that have sought refuge in Yemen 
after the start of the civil war in their country, he said. 
  Southern forces used attack a military hospital in one of 
the 
northern regions, he added [sentence as received]. 

</TEXT>

