<DOCNO> FBIS4-59078 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes091_j_94029" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-091 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  5 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Welcomes International Efforts To End Fighting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Welcomes International Efforts To End Fighting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA0605162294 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2045 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA0605162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni Socialist Party's [YSP] political bureau 
has welcomed the efforts of brothers and friends to stop the 
in-fighting and war ignited by the secessionist military family 
in Sanaa between the sons of the Yemeni people and their armed 
forces. It confirmed that the response to these Arab and 
international efforts and initiatives was prompted by the Yemeni 
people's interest to preserve their gains and unity, and 
safeguard their armed forces economic structures and the 
citizens' souls. It was in this respect that the YSP political 
bureau responded to the calls by the United States, French, 
Egyptian, and Algerian Governments, and expressed its hope that 
these calls and efforts would receive the support of all the 
sides concerned at a time when the battles are leading towards 
comprehensive destruction. 
  In keeping with these efforts, the militant brother, 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid, secretary general of the YSP Central Committee, 
continued his contacts with a number of Arab presidents, 
including the Egyptian president, Muhammad Husni Mubarak, the 
Syrian president, Hafiz al-Asad, and the Libyan president, 
Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi. He briefed them on developments in Yemen 
and the bloody battles at the various axes of fighting. He 
thanked them for their concern for Yemen and confirmed the YSP's 
compliance with any effort to reflect Yemen and the Yemeni 
people from the devastation of war and in-fighting among the 
brothers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

