<H3> <TI>   House Asks Embassies, Others Not To Deal With Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House Asks Embassies, Others Not To Deal With Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805110494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1030 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives met today in the 
presence of the parliamentary bloc of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party. It discussed the issue of the illegitimate and 
unconstitutional moves and activities abroad by brother Haydar 
Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, the prime minister. The conferees supported 
the issuance of a circular to all embassies and official and 
diplomatic quarters in the sisterly and friendly countries and 
the international bodies and institutions, asking them not to 
officially deal with brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas, 
currently abroad, because he was not on an official mission. He 
was not entrusted to undertake such a mission by the legitimate 
and constitutional political leadership nor has this mission 
been approved by the Council of Ministers. 

</TEXT>

