<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Speaker Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Speaker Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005214994 Kuwait KUNA in Arabic 2026 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1005214994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuwait KUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Riyadh, 10 May, KUNA -- Shaykh 'Abdallah 
al-Ahmar, the speaker of the Yemeni Parliament has said that he 
is visiting Riyadh to clarify what is happening in Yemen "within 
the framework of the solid and traditional relations between the 
two countries." 
  Shaykh al-Ahmar, who arrived in Riyadh tonight, told KUNA: 
"We have not come to look for mediation." In reply to a 
question whether he was hoping for a Saudi role to solve the 
Yemeni crisis, Shaykh al-Ahmar said: "The Kingdom of Saudi 
Arabia strives to do good deeds always and everywhere." 
  Shaykh al-Ahmar, who is accompanied by the planning 
minister, 
'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani, is carrying a message for King Fahd 
Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz, custodian of the two holy mosques, from the 
Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, on "the developments of 
the situation in Yemen and issues of mutual interest." 
  Shaykh al-Ahmar has denied the existence of Arab mediation 
to 
resolve the conflict, indicating that "since he left Sanaa this 
afternoon he has not heard of any mediation." He added that 
"the conflict has been decided militarily after the northern 
troops reached Shaykh 'Uthman area, situated north of Aden." He 
further said that the southern air base of al-'Anad had been 
captured and "it was brought under control this afternoon." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

