<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Says Arab League Session `Unjustified' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Says Arab League Session `Unjustified' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705080994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0627 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0705080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 May (MENA)--Foreign Minister Muhammad Salih 
Basindwah stated that the Arab League's emergency meeting to 
discuss sending Arab forces to disengage Yemen's combatants is 
unjustified, noting that Yemen's situation is an internal affair 
and not a conflict between two separate states. 
  In an interview with the BBC today, he said limited fighting 
is now taking place in Abyan and Lahij provinces between the 
government forces and what he termed as a group of the 
separatist forces. 
  He said Scud missiles had been used against Sanaa and other 
cities in the north and that aircraft from the south had raided 
the capital Sanaa. He added that of the aircraft that had 
raided the capital and other cities ten were shot down. 
  He said the decision to dismiss Yemeni Vice President 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid was permitted by the constitution, which empowers 
the State Council to make such decisions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

