<H3> <TI>   Arab League Secretary Phones Basindwah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arab League Secretary Phones Basindwah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705193794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1900 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0705193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 7 May (MENA) -- Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid telephoned Foreign Minister Ahmad Salim 
Basindwah to inform him of the resolution passed earlier today 
by an Arab League extraordinary session on Yemen. 
  Tal'at Hamid, press adviser to the Arab League secretary 
general, has stated that Basindwah pointed out that Yemen 
welcomes the Arab League's resolution. Basindwah voiced Yemen's 
readiness to receive a delegation from the Arab League's General 
Secretariat and to adopt the necessary measures as soon as 
possible to secure the arrival of the delegation in Sanaa. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid has formed a high-level delegation from 
the 
League's Secretariat led by Major General Sa'id Bayraqdar, 
assistant secretary general for military affairs, and assigned 
it to exert efforts to stop the fighting there, but the closure 
of the Sanaa airport precluded the arrival of the delegation. 
  During the telephone conversation, Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid 
underscored the interest of all member states to end the 
fighting and find an appropriate settlement of the Yemeni crisis 
that could ensure the unity, security, and stability of Yemen. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

