  [Text] Foreign Minister brother Muhammad Salim Basindwah 
has denied radio and news agency reports that an Arab League 
delegation will arrive in Sanaa to mediate a cease-fire. The 
brother foreign minister objected to the Arab League meeting to 
discuss an internal Yemeni affair, viewing such a meeting as a 
serious precedent that could extend to other Arab countries in 
the future. The brother foreign minister emphasized that what 
is taking place in Yemen is just a confrontation by the 
legitimate authorities of a rebel group that has deviated from 
constitutional legitimacy. 

