<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Discusses `Important' Oil, Electricity Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Discusses `Important' Oil, Electricity Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805124894 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0805124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers held an extraordinary 
meeting today under Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, deputy prime 
minister industry minister, and acting prime minister. 
  The Council of Ministers reviewed developments in the 
general 
situation in the country since the rebelling secessionist gang, 
led by the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP], exploded the situation 
militarily with the objective of returning the country to pre-22 
May 1990 status. 
  During this meeting, the Council of Ministers praised the 
heroism of the Armed Forces soldiers, noncommissioned officers, 
and officers, the forces of unity and Constitutional legitimacy. 
The Council also praised the people's rallying around these 
forces. 
  The Council of Ministers commended all the decisions and 
legitimate measures adopted by the Presidential Council and the 
House of Representatives. 
  The Council of Ministers discussed a number of important 
issues, particularly issues related to supply, trade, 
electricity, and oil, and took the necessary measures on them in 
order to reinforce the course of normal life in all governorates. 

</TEXT>

