<H3> <TI>   House of Representatives Discusses Oil Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    House of Representatives Discusses Oil Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005131394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives met in an ordinary 
session this morning under brother Muhammad al-Khadim al-Wajih, 
member of the House's Speakership Council. The meeting was held 
in the context of the third round of the second phase of the 
council's first term. 
  At the outset of the session, the deputies reviewed and 
ratified the minutes of the previous meeting. They then 
discussed oil issues in terms of finance, administration, 
accounting, and consumption. 
  The House referred the matter to its Financial Affairs and 
Economic Subcommittees for scrutiny and to collect data and 
information before submitting a detailed report. 
  Today's session was attended by brother 'Adil Khurshid, 
undersecretary at the Ministry of Oil and Mineral Resources, and 
'Askar 'Ali al-Dahiri, chairman of the Technical and 
Consultative Office at the ministry. 

</TEXT>

