<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Praises Iran, Urges Closer Parliamentary Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Speaker Praises Iran, Urges Closer Parliamentary Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0905205994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1930 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0905205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The speaker of the Libyan Parliament described 
Iran's policy of defending the rights of Muslims and Islamic 
values as independent and a source of pride for the world of 
Islam. 
  At a meeting in Tripoli with our country's ambassador, which 
was for the purpose of handing over a written message from 
Majles Speaker Nateq-Nuri, the Libyan parliamentary speaker 
said: The free will and resistance of Islamic Iran in dealing 
with the problems of the world of Islam, and her defense of 
Islamic values, raise the morale of Muslim peoples in tackling 
problems. 
  At the meeting, our country's ambassador outlined the common 
viewpoints of Iran and Libya on important global issues. He 
called for more activity by the two countries' parliamentary 
friendship groups. 
  Also a written message from Nateq-Nuri about the painful and 
dangerous conditions in Bosnia-Herzegovina was handed to Nabih 
Birri, the speaker of the Lebanese National Assembly. 
  According to a Central News Unit report from Beirut, our 
country's ambassador in Beirut told reporters on Monday, after 
delivering the message, that he had discussed ways of 
cooperation and coordination between parliaments of Islamic 
countries in the defense of the innocent and oppressed people of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and to bring to an end to the massacre of 
that Muslim nation. 
  Our country's ambassador added: The Gaza-Jericho agreement 
is, in fact, a security agreement, which is aimed at 'Arafat's 
police crushing the Intifadah and fighting the Palestinian 
nation. 

</TEXT>

