<H3> <TI>   Jericho Area Commander on Police Crossing Delay </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jericho Area Commander on Police Crossing Delay </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005202894 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1700 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview With Brigadier General Isma'il Jabr, Palestinian </F>
commander of the Jericho area police, by Salim 'Ali Dhiyab in 
the Jordan valley on 10 May -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Jabr] The crossing of Palestinian police to 
Jericho was to have taken place today. A previously scheduled 
meeting was held today with the Israeli side with the objective 
of setting the crossing into motion. However, the Israeli side 
said it could not let the entry of the Palestinian police force 
go ahead, citing political reasons. However, we managed to 
smooth over some snags holding up the entry. For our part, we 
informed them we were poised to crossing at the very moment we 
were holding talks with them. 
  [Dhiyab] What were the most important points you agreed on 
in your talks with the Israeli side? 
  [Jabr] The Israeli side said it would refer to its command 
for clearance to start the crossing. As I have said, we told 
them we were ready to move as of yesterday. 

</TEXT>

