<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Service Contracts Signed With Foreign Firms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Service Contracts Signed With Foreign Firms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0705061294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0400 GMT 7 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0705061294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Palestinian negotiator Jamil al-Tarifi says the 
Palestine National Authority has signed new temporary contracts 
with the Israeli water, electricity, and communications 
companies to continue their services in Gaza and Jericho until 
the PLO takes over. He says he expects the takeover to take 
place on 17 May. 
  According to al-Tarifi, the Palestinian authority has 
already 
signed contracts with large foreign companies to supply the 
self-rule areas with the services they need. A Canadian company 
will supply Gaza with 100 megawatts of electricity from a ship 
off the Gaza coast, and after two months, the company will 
double its supply. 
  Jericho will continue to receive electricity from Israel 
until an alternative becomes available. The Meqorot water 
company has also promised to continue supplying water until an 
alternative is found. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 0500 GMT on 7 May cites 
al-Tarifi as announcing that "a French company by the name of 
(Marbec) will supply the Strip with fuel and build a small oil 
refinery."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

