<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Moves Media Activity From Amman to Damascus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Moves Media Activity From Amman to Damascus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0705101194 Amman SHIHAN in Arabic 7-13 May 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> JN0705101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman SHIHAN </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Muhammad Nazzal, Hamas representative in Jordan, has 
said Hamas in the Gaza Strip and the West Bank will not take up 
arms against either the self-rule authority or Fatah members. 
  In the last press statement he made in Amman before Hamas 
moved its media activity from Amman to Damascus, Nazzal said: 
We only call on the self-rule authority not to stand against 
Hamas Movement's program calling for the end of Israeli 
occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

