<H3> <TI>   PFLP Claims Attack on Israeli Bus Near Ramallah </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PFLP Claims Attack on Israeli Bus Near Ramallah </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105094394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 0900 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine 
[PFLP] has claimed responsibility for the attack on an Israeli 
bus near Ramallah in the occupied West Bank. A statement signed 
by the vanguards of comrade martyr Wadi' Haddad was distributed 
in the occupied Palestinian territories today. The statement 
says that in continuation of the policy of revolutionary 
violence and armed militancy, the Ibrahim al-Ra'i group has 
attacked an Israeli bus carrying Zionist settlers. 
  In reference to the Palestinian self-rule agreement, the 
statement says that agreements will not protect the usurpers of 
our territories and displacers of our people. 

</TEXT>

