<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   France Arrests FIS `Activist' Transporting Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    France Arrests FIS `Activist' Transporting Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1005200294 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1005200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Regarding reports on terrorism, the Algerian 
national Abdelkrim Boutrif appeared before a French magistrate 
today and was remanded in custody. Boutrif was arrested on the 
French-German border in possession of a quantity of weapons and 
ammunition. In the trunk of his car police discovered over 129 
sticks of dynamite, about 100 detonators, some 3,000 bullets, 
three automatic pistols, night vision binoculars, and 14 two-way 
radios. 
  Abdelkrim Boutrif is 34 and an activist in the banned 
Islamic 
Salvation Front. His mission was to drive the car and its 
contents all the way to Spain, from where this arsenal would 
have been taken to Algeria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

