<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Baz Explains Position on Peace to Israelis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Baz Explains Position on Peace to Israelis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1005110094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1005110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 10 May (MENA)--Dr. Usamah al-Baz, first 
Foreign Ministry under secretary and director of the President's 
Office for Political Affairs, has stated the need to broaden the 
Middle East peace process to involve every track, particularly 
the Syrian-Israeli track. Dr. al-Baz pointed out that 
comprehensive and just peace will be achieved only if all these 
tracks are included. 
  Dr. al-Baz made these remarks during a meeting here today 
with a delegation of new heads of Israeli diplomatic missions to 
several countries, which is visiting Cairo. He stressed that 
Egypt is trying to overcome the obstacles obstructing the peace 
process, particularly along the Syrian-Israeli track. Dr. 
al-Baz explained to the delegation Egypt's position on various 
Arab, African, and international issues. 
  Israeli Ambassador in Cairo David Sultan said the Israeli 
diplomats wanted, before starting their new jobs abroad, to 
learn Egypt's views on the peace process in the region and the 
negotiations relating to this process. The ambassador noted 
that the delegation's visit to Egypt will last three days. 

</TEXT>

