<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Official Denies Troop Presence in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Official Denies Troop Presence in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1005172194 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in 
Arabic 1500 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1005172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ambassador 'Umar Yusuf Baridu, the first under 
secretary of the Foreign Ministry, has denied reports carried by 
some news agencies and media organs on Sudanese troops taking 
part in the ongoing war in Yemen. He added that the propagation 
of such allegations may be aimed at widening the scope of the 
war using it as a pretext for foreign intervention in the 
ongoing conflict in Yemen. Ambassador Baridu reaffirmed Sudan's 
principled attitude toward what was taking place in fraternal 
Yemen as exemplified by Sudan's eagerness to see the crisis 
approached within a Yemeni context. He said Sudan's position 
was based on clear and specific principles, including 
noninterference in the internal affairs of states and commitment 
to the charters of the United Nations, OAU, and the Arab League. 

</TEXT>

