<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Meets Austrian Minister, IAEA Director </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Aziz Meets Austrian Minister, IAEA Director </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005120294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1800 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz met with Austrian 
Foreign Minister Alois Mock in Vienna today. They discussed the 
obligations the UN Security Council should fulfill toward Iraq, 
particularly in terms of implementing Paragraph 22 of Resolution 
687 and lifting the unfair embargo since Iraq has implemented 
all pertinent clauses in Resolution 687. 
  They also discussed bilateral ties. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz also met with Hans Blix, 
director general of the International Atomic Energy Agency 
[IAEA]. They discussed the IAEA's responsibility to acknowledge 
what Iraq had implemented in the field as stipulated by 
Resolution 687 and the need to fully inform the UN Security 
Council of such as soon as possible, so the Security Council can 
assume its responsibility and immediately start considering the 
implementation of Paragraph 22 of Resolution 687 as soon as 
possible. 
  The two meetings were attended by Barzan al-Tikriti, Iraq's 
permanent envoy to the UN Headquarters in Geneva; Dr. Rahim al- 
Kital, Iraq's ambassador to Austria; and the deputy director of 
the Iraqi Atomic Energy Organization. Professor Zifferero and a 
number of assistants to the IAEA director attended the meeting 
for the IAEA. 

</TEXT>

