<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Given Airspace, `Hostile Publications' Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Given Airspace, `Hostile Publications' Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0805105294 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0935 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0805105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, 8 May (INA)--Iraq has protested to the 
United Nations against U.S. aircraft continuing to violate 
Iraq's airspace for purposes of surveillance and provocation. 
  In a letter he sent to UN Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali yesterday, Iraq's permanent UN representative, said 
these aircraft carried out 323 hostile sorties over large areas 
of northern and southern Iraq on 21, 22, 23, 28, 29, and 30 
April. 
  The memorandum also said that a drone fell on the village of 
Berminkah east of Mosul on 28 April and that hostile enemy 
dropped hostile publications over al-Ta'mim Governorate on the 
same day. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

