<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Health Minister Mubarak Attends WHO Meeting in Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Health Minister Mubarak Attends WHO Meeting in Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Blames Embargo for Health Conditions </H4>

<F P=102> JN0605181294 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1600 GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0605181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Health Minister Dr. Umid Midhat Mubarak has blamed 
the persistent sanctions for the progressive deterioration in 
health conditions in Iraq, citing a dearth in medicines and 
medical facilities. 
  The minister was speaking at a news conference in Geneva, 
where he is attending a World Health Organization conference. 
Mubarak said the rising incidence of diseases and deaths among 
children in particular is supported by reports drawn up by 
international organizations. 
  Iraq has satisfied the conditions laid down by UN Security 
Council resolutions, and is now, therefore, eligible for imports 
of food and medicines. Certain quarters, however, are blocking 
these deliveries, said the minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

