<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Health Minister Mubarak Attends WHO Meeting in Geneva </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Health Minister Mubarak Attends WHO Meeting in Geneva </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Urges Mediation To Release Funds </H4>

<F P=102> JN0705134994 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1205 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0705134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, 7 May (INA)--Iraq has urged the WHO to 
intercede with the UN Security Council to secure the release of 
frozen Iraqi assets, so that it can purchase medicines and other 
basic human necessities and medical supplies. 
  In an address to the 47th WHO session currently convening in 
Geneva, Health Minister Umid Midhat Mubarak urged the 
international community to speak out against the continued 
blockade imposed on Iraq since Iraq has honored its commitments 
in accordance with the pertinent UN Security Council resolutions. 
  The health minister reviewed the health situation in Iraq in 
light of the unjust economic blockade imposed on the Iraqi 
people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

