<H3> <TI>   Saddam Allocates 8 Million Dinars To Aid Poor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Allocates 8 Million Dinars To Aid Poor </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005122094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1030 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1005122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn has ordered the 
allocation of 8 million dinars for poor families in the 
governorates of al-Najaf, al-Muthanna, and al-Ramadi due to the 
approach of the blessed 'Id al-Adha. 
  The comrade secretaries of al-Najaf, al-Muthanna, al-Anbar, 
and al-Jazirah branches of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party said 
leader President Saddam Husayn's generous contribution confirms 
his excellency's interest in alleviating the suffering of his 
people. This suffering is a result of the continued blockade 
imposed on the people of Iraq and seeks to infringe on their 
steadfastness and free will. 

</TEXT>

