  [Text] Jalal Talabani, secretary general of the Patriotic 
Union of Kurdistan [PUK], has addressed an appeal to the 
peshmerga forces in Kurdistan and the Kurdish masses. He 
stressed the need for unity and solidarity among the Kurdish 
people in general and between the PUK and the Kurdish Democratic 
Party in particular. 
  Talabani said that making the democratic experience in 
Kurdistan a success and the survival and promotion of the 
government of Kurdistan is contingent upon the unity of the 
people's ranks. He emphasized that all resources must be 
devoted to protecting liberated Kurdistan and liberating the 
country from the dictatorship and establishing a federal 
democratic Iraq. He called on the struggling Kurdish parties to 
enhance their struggle and efforts to entrench peace and 
fraternity in dear Kurdistan. 

