<H3> <TI>   Coalition's `Silence' on Kurdish Fighting Criticized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coalition's `Silence' on Kurdish Fighting Criticized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0605115494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0938 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0605115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 6 May (INA)--The newspaper AL-'IRAQ has 
said the coalition forces' silence on the massacres of Iraq's 
Kurds, represented by the conflict between the Talabani and 
Barzani groups, exposes the false humanitarian slogans 
Washington and its allies used as a cover to enter into 
Kurdistan. 
  In its editorial today, the paper emphasizes that the 
continued annihilation of Kurds in the fierce and ongoing 
confrontations between the Jalal Talabani and Mas'ud Barzani 
groups sheds light on the serious conspiracy concocted by the 
colonialist and Zionist circles against Iraq and its people. 
  AL-'IRAQ adds that the comprehensive and large-scale 
fighting 
between the Talabani and Barzani gangs reflects the miserable 
situation created by the erroneous circumstances in the absence 
of order and law in the area. 
  The paper wonders about foreign forces' role in confronting 
the scandals and terrible crimes to which the sons of Kurdistan 
are being subjected. These forces came on the pretext of 
immediately intervening and protecting the Kurds, if they are 
subjected to any military operation. 
  Suffice it to say that turning a blind eye to the ongoing 
massacres of Iraq's Kurds is a flagrant war against the Kurds 
targeting their lives, existence, fate, and their future, the 
paper notes. 
  AL-'IRAQ describes the position of the foreign forces, which 
are idly watching the slaughtering of Iraq's Kurds at the hands 
of the Talabani and Barzani gangs, as a new formula of 
imperialist-Zionist hypocrisy and a form of intrigue, lies, 
distortion, falsification, reversal of realities, and 
concealment of facts away from the world public opinion. 

</TEXT>

