<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Marshlands Said Almost Dry; Residents Leaving </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Marshlands Said Almost Dry; Residents Leaving </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705152894 (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0705152894 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of Iraqi Islamic Revolution 
in Arabic 1430 GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Iraqi mujahidin sources in southern Iraq said that 
90 percent of the marshlands in the south have been dried up and 
that these areas have no water in them except for some parts of 
the marshlands of al-Basrah and al-'Amarah. In an attempt to 
describe the bad conditions the marshland dwellers are living 
in, the sources said that drying up the marshlands has pushed 
most of the people there to migrate to other areas. The 
terrorist regime in Baghdad has also transferred some of the 
marshland dwellers to unknown districts. 
  In another report, an Iraqi mujahid said that the surprise 
attack the mujahidin forces carried out recently on the 
headquarters of the 10th Battalion in the north al-Qurnah led to 
the elimination of two platoons and the killing of the commander 
of the battalion. In these operations, the mujahidin seized a 
number of mortars, some communications equipment, and some 
military documents. 

</TEXT>

