<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Harvest Preparations in Babil Governorate Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Harvest Preparations in Babil Governorate Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1005192694 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 6 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> JN1005192694 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-THAWRAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by correspondent Muhammad al-Talibi] </F>
  [Text] Babil -- The largest wheat and barley harvest 
campaign to be witnessed by Babil Governorate this year has 
begun with the participation of thousands of peasants and 
farmers. 
  Sa'id Salman al-Fadili, director of Babil Agriculture 
Department, said some 14 committee have been formed to supervise 
harvest operations and to provide the necessary means of 
transport to ensure the success of the campaign, which covers 
293,000 donums and in which 105 harvesters will be used. Fuel 
and spare parts have also been ensured for the harvesters. He 
added that trucks have been provided to transport grains 
directly to silos and government receiving centers, and the 
Agriculture Department's teams have been instructed to join the 
campaign to follow its progress. 
  Al-Fadili said a mobile repair workshop with mechanics will 
accompany the harvesters, which can be transferred from one 
administrative unit to another if necessary to achieve a balance 
and to complete the harvest in all areas at once. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

