<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Preparations in Ninawa Inspected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preparations in Ninawa Inspected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105092994 Baghdad AL-THAWRAH in Arabic 6 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> JN1105092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad AL-THAWRAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Ninawa -- Trade Minister Muhammad Mahdi Salih 
and Agriculture Minister Bashir 'Alwan Hammadi have discussed 
with Ninawa Governor Staff Lt Gen 'Abd-al-Wahid Shannan Al Ribat 
the final preparations that have been made to begin the campaign 
for harvesting and marketing wheat and barley crops in the 
governorate. 
  This was during an expanded meeting of the governorate's 
Central Harvest and Marketing Committee which was attended by 
comrade Najm 'Abdallah al-'Iraqi, secretary of the Ba'th Party 
Ninawa Branch; 'Abd-al-Hamid al-Sayigh, secretary of the Mosul 
branch; several directors from the two ministries, heads of the 
departments concerned with the campaign; and representatives of 
the Federation of Peasant Cooperative Societies in the 
governorate. 
  The ministers praised the efforts and preparations that have 
been made by the Central Committee and the subcommittees in the 
Ninawa and Mosul party branches and other participant sides for 
the success of the harvest and marketing campaign in fulfillment 
of leader President Saddam Husayn's desire to ensure the 
campaign's requirements throughout our country, especially in 
Ninawa Governorate, in order to guarantee food for the people 
and to defeat the unfair blockade on our country. [passage 
omitted] 
  It was decided during the meeting to increase the present 
storage capacity so as to absorb the entire quantity of grain to 
be bought. Some 300 trucks have been ensured for transporting 
grain. This is in addition to transport by rail. 
  The agriculture minister affirmed that Ninawa will be the 
nail in the coffin of the food embargo imposed on our people. 
He said: This governorate, which leader President Saddam Husayn 
called "the bread basket of great Iraq," will play a major role 
in guaranteeing people's food. 
  The ministers of trade and agriculture, accompanied by the 
governor, then made a tour of several harvest and marketing 
areas to inspect the preparations which have been made. The 
areas included: al-Hadr, al-Qayyarah, Shawrah, Mahallabiyah, 
Tall 'Afar, Sinjar, al-Bi'aj, Tall Kayf, and Ba'shiqah. 

</TEXT>

