<F P=100> Nepal &amp; Bhutan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Gets Clean Bill of Health </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Gets Clean Bill of Health </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0705121894 Hong Kong AFP in English 1107 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0705121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kathmandu, May 7 (AFP) -- Prime Minister Girija 
Prasad Koirala of Nepal returned home in high spirits from the 
United States Saturday after a medical checkup there which gave 
him the all clear. 
  Talking to newsmen at the airport soon after his arrival 
Koirala said "I am not suffering from any diseases and my health 
condition is now normal. I will be joining official duties from 
Sunday." 
  Koirala's personal physician, Madhu Ghimire, said the prime 
minister had undergone a detailed checkup at the Walter Reed 
Hospital in Washington and had been given a clean bill of health. 
  Koirala was advised to go to the United States for the 
checks 
after he suffered a series of fainting spells earlier this year. 
He left on April 22. 
  Before heading home Koirala stopped in Germany for two days 
to rest, a member of his family said. 

</TEXT>

