  [Text] The Senate has issued a statement deeply deploring 
the sad events pitting brother against brother in Yemen. The 
Senate, the statement said, regrets the high toll of casualties 
and the scale of destruction caused to the infrastructure that 
was built thanks to the sacrifices of the brotherly Yemeni 
people as they marched toward unity, development, and 
construction. The Senate called on the Yemeni brothers to let 
wisdom and dialogue prevail and address the roots of their 
disagreements to preserve the country's unity and spare the 
lives of Yemenis so that they can pursue the process of unity 
and construction and Yemen can continue to play its key pan-Arab 
role. 

