<H3> <TI>   National Airline Suspends Flights to Sanaa, Aden </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Airline Suspends Flights to Sanaa, Aden </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0705063894 Amman JORDAN TIMES in English 7 May p 3 </F>
<F P=103> JN0705063894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman JORDAN TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By JORDAN TIMES staff reporter Elia Nasrallah] </F>
  [Excerpt] Amman--Royal Jordanian's [RJ] twice weekly 
flights to Sanaa and Aden in north and south Yemen are suspended 
until the airports in the Arab country are officially operating 
normally again, according to a spokesman for the national 
airline Friday [6 May]. 
  The military in Yemen have taken control of the airports and 
closed them to civilian flights until further notice; until then 
no RJ aircraft can fly to Yemen, Munib Toukan, RJ assistant vice 
president for public relations, told the JORDAN TIMES. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

