<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Reports Cabinet Session Proceedings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Reports Cabinet Session Proceedings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN0705135894 Amman Radio Jordan in English 1100 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0705135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Prime Minister 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali has 
chaired a cabinet meeting on a number of issues. Dr. al-Majali 
briefed cabinet ministers on the visit to Amman by PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat and his talks with his majesty the king. He also 
gave a report on the visit of Japanese Foreign Minister Koji 
Kakizawa, who has pledged his country's support to the kingdom 
in various aspects. 
  During the meeting, Minister of State for Foreign Affairs, 
Talal al-Hasan, presented a report on the signing of the 
PLO-Israel agreement on implementing self-rule in Gaza and 
Jericho. Mr. al-Hasan represented Jordan in the signing 
ceremony in Cairo on Wednesday. 
  Trade and Industry Minister Dr. Rima Khalaf submitted a 
report on a Jordanian-French cooperation seminar held in Paris. 
She asserted France's desire to develop economic and investment 
cooperation in the public and private sectors. 
  The cabinet also listened to a report by Minister of 
Education Khalid al-'Umari on the meetings of UNESCO's executive 
council held in Paris. He said the council has underlined 
educational programs for all and the importance of democracy and 
international tolerance. 
  Cabinet ministers discussed other issues on the agenda and 
took appropriate measures. 

</TEXT>

