BFN 

  [Text] This morning in Pretoria, President of State 'Ezer 
Weizman held brief meetings with Cuban President Fidel Castro, 
Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto, and with the sultan of 
Oman. President Weizman told our correspondent Gid'on Kouts 
that Castro expressed an interest in ties with Israel. Castro 
added that the agreement Israel and the Palestinians had signed 
pleased him very much and that recently he met many Israelis. 
President Weizman invited the Cuban leader to visit Israel. 
  Pakistani Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto also expressed 
pleasure over the agreement between Israel and the Palestinians. 
In her conversation with Weizman, she did not rule out contacts 
between Pakistan and Israel. 

