<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cypriot Parliamentarians Meet Rabin, Peres </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cypriot Parliamentarians Meet Rabin, Peres </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0905112694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0905112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The House of Representatives multiparty delegation 
led by House President Alexis Galanos, now on an official visit 
to Israel, today began high-level contacts with Israeli 
officials. The delegation was received this morning by Israeli 
Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and then met with Foreign Minister 
Shim'on Peres. 
  Both Mr. Rabin and Mr. Peres stressed the importance they 
attach to the visit and added that it will contribute to the 
development of Cypriot-Israeli relations. They also stated that 
the visit opens doors in the right direction. 
  Referring to the Cyprus issue, Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin 
wished for an early reunification of the island and stressed 
that it is important for there to be one state entity in Cyprus, 
where the principle of rule by the majority should prevail. 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres stressed the need to safeguard 
the unity of the Republic of Cyprus through intercommunal talks. 
However, he added that Israel is interested in its relations 
with Turkey and that it should preserve and safeguard them. 
  In a statement to the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation, 
Shim'on Peres said that Cyprus has a bright future. He also 
expressed the conviction that there is enough prudence on the 
island for the existing dispute to be resolve soon. Peres 
further noted that Cyprus can become a significant center for 
the exchange of ideas and trade. 

</TEXT>

