Highness Shaykh 'Isa Bin-Salman Al Khalifah, this morning 
received Robert Pelletreau, U.S. assistant secretary of state 
for Near East and North African affairs, and his delegation 
currently visiting Bahrain. 
  During the meeting, his highness the amir praised the deep, 
close relations between Bahrain and the United States. He 
expressed satisfaction with the level of the existing bilateral 
relations of friendship and cooperation and their importance in 
maintaining the Gulf region's security and stability. 
  Mr. Pelletreau briefed his Highness Amir 'Isa on the latest 
developments in Yemen and the importance of containing the 
current crisis to prevent it from being exacerbated [words 
indistinct] dangerous repercussions on the future of Yemen and 
regional security and stability. 
  The two sides reviewed bilateral relations and ways to 
bolster them in various domains. They also reviewed the latest 
[words indistinct] Arab, and international developments. 
  The meeting was attended by Foreign Minister Shaykh Muhammad 
Bin- Mubarak Al Khalifah, Interior Minister Muhammad 
Bin-Khalifah Al Khalifah, Communications Minister 'Ali 
Bin-Khalifah Al Khalifah, Foreign Ministry Under Secretary Ghazi 
Muhammad al-Qusaybi, and the U.S. charge d'affaires in Bahrain. 

