<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Manama, 10 May (WAKH) -- Shaykh Muhammad Bin-Mubarak 
Al Khalifah, Bahraini minister of foreign affairs, today 
received Robert Pelletreau, the U.S. assistant secretary of 
state for Near East and North African affairs, who is currently 
visiting Bahrain. 
  During the meeting, the Bahraini foreign minister and 
Pelletreau exchanged views on friendly relations and cooperation 
between the State of Bahrain and the United States, ways of 
enhancing them for the benefit of the two friendly countries and 
peoples, and the issue of stability in the region. 
  They also reviewed several issues of common interest, 
especially those pertaining to the situation in the Gulf region; 
current developments in Yemen; the peace process in the Middle 
East in light of the signing of the recent Palestinian-Israeli 
accord in Cairo; and the importance of activating negotiations 
on other tracks in order to achieve a just, comprehensive, and 
lasting peace in the Middle East. 

</TEXT>

