<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Saddam Reportedly `Unable' To Meet Palestinian Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saddam Reportedly `Unable' To Meet Palestinian Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105182594 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 9 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1105182594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AL-MAJD has learned that certain snags have 
prevented the visit of a high-level Palestinian political 
delegation to Baghdad. Primarily, Iraqi President Saddam Husayn 
has apologized for being unable to receive the delegation at 
present. 
  On the other hand, a Palestinian military delegation, which 
has been visiting Baghdad for more than two weeks, discussed 
technical issues only at the level of liaison officers between 
the forces of the Palestine Liberation Army and the Iraqi Army. 
  The troops of the Palestine Liberation Army deployed in Iraq 
will be the first to enter Jericho through Jordan this week. 
  Iraq did not agree to allow these forces to leave and to 
take 
along all their weapons. It allowed them to carry personal 
weapons only, that is, a pistol for officers. It also allowed 
them to carry 60 rifles as they leave the Iraqi-Jordanian border. 
  The PLO tried to acquire light weapons and ammunitions from 
Jordan. While discussing this issue, Greece said it was willing 
to provide the Palestinian police force with light weapons. 

</TEXT>

