Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Aziz Arrives in New York for Talks on Ending Blockade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Aziz Arrives in New York for Talks on Ending Blockade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205102494 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0850 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1205102494 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] New York, 12 May (INA)--Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz will today begin a series of political talks with the 
president and members of the UN Security Council on lifting the 
unjust blockade imposed on Iraq. 
  INA correspondent in New York said that Tariq 'Aziz will 
meet 
with Ibrahim Gambari, Nigeria's ambassador to the United Nations 
and current UN Security Council president, at the UN 
headquarters in New York today. 
  Later today, the deputy prime minister is scheduled to 
separately meet with China's Ambassador Li Zhaoxing, French 
Ambassador Jean-Bernard Merimee, and Omani Ambassador Salim 
Bin-Muhammad al-Qusaybi. 
  Tariq 'Aziz arrived in New York last night from Vienna after 
he held talks with Hans Blix, director general of the 
International Atomic Energy Agency. 

</TEXT>

