<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   APF Rejects Resettlement, Asks Lebanon for Help </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    APF Rejects Resettlement, Asks Lebanon for Help </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105194394 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1700 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio Monte Carlo </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sana' al-Imam from Damascus] </F>
  [Text] The Alliance of Palestinian Forces [APF] Central 
Command has held a meeting in the presence of the 
representatives of this alliance in Lebanon. The discussion 
dealt with the serious repercussions the Cairo agreement will 
have on the Palestinians in the diaspora. 
  A statement issued by the conferees emphasized that this 
agreement endangers the status of the diaspora Palestinians, 
particularly in the camps in Lebanon. In this respect, the 
secretaries general of the 10 Palestinian factions called on the 
Lebanese Government and the Lebanese nationalist and Islamic 
forces to enhance the cohesion and the unity of blood enshrined 
by the Lebanese and Palestinian people, and to defend the 
Palestinian people's right to repatriation. In their message to 
the Lebanese Government, the factions reiterated their rejection 
of resettlement in Lebanon. The 10 factions said they hope the 
Lebanese Government will help the Palestinian people in Lebanon 
solve the problems they face, treat Palestinians as equals with 
the Lebanese concerning job opportunities, and reconstruct the 
camps after the United Nations Relief and Works Agency [UNRWA] 
reduced its aid to these camps. The factions called on UNRWA to 
continue its task of providing various services to the 
Palestinian people. 
  Democratic Front for the Liberation of Palestine [DFLP] 
sources said other meetings will be held in Lebanon between the 
10 factions, the Lebanese Government, and UNRWA representatives 
to tackle these issues. 

</TEXT>

