<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister on Transitional Council, Early Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister on Transitional Council, Early Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105212494 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105212494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a statement to Channel 3 of Algiers radio, Prime 
Minister Mokdad Sifi answered a number of questions on various 
topics such as the national economic and social council, which 
he described as a step forward. The prime minister stated that 
the National Transitional Council will be installed soon and 
that sufficient time has been given to all parties to consider 
the issue of participating in the council. 
  Regarding the priorities of his government's agenda, Mr. 
Sifi 
stressed three points: economic stimulation, the strengthening 
of the state's institutions, and national solidarity. 
  In his reply to a question on the possibility of calling 
early elections before the end of the transitional period, the 
prime minister said that the matter depends mainly on the 
existence of stable conditions. 
  On the agreement with the IMF, which he preferred to call 
the 
Algerian restructuring program, which was accepted by the IMF, 
the prime minister said that it has positive and negative 
effects and that we should wait for the talks with the Paris 
Club and the duration of the debt rescheduling period. He added 
that there is a plan to help low-income social classes. 
  Regarding Algeria's educational system, the prime minister 
expressed hope that it would be changed from within the regime 
itself with the participation of the administration, staff, and 
parents. 
  In conclusion, the prime minister said that he prefers a 
policy of consultation with the administration and all parties. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

