<H3> <TI>   AL-AHRAM Warns Against `Interference' in Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    AL-AHRAM Warns Against `Interference' in Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205070994 Cairo MENA in English 0615 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1205070994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, May 12 (MENA)--"AL-AHRAM" warned, in its 
editorial today, against playing with fire in Yemen. 
  South Yemen said Arab elements are fighting alongside north 
Yemenis, adding that these elements will appear on Aden 
television screens, the paper said. 
  This version has several serious implications. 
  According to this version, troops from an Arab country may 
be 
fighting beside the forces of the north along with Arab elements 
living in Yemen. 
  The report may, in the meantime, be a call for 
internationalizing the crisis, the paper added. 
  In any case there should be a warning against any 
interference in the Yemeni war in the way reported by the 
southerners, the paper said. 

