<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Evacuate Citizens From Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Evacuate Citizens From Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1105205894 Nairobi KNA in English 1755 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1105205894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nairobi KNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Khartoum, 11 May (KNA/PANA) -- Alarmed over the 
fate of tens of thousands of its nationals working in embattled 
Yemen, the Sudanese Government has decided to evacuate those of 
them who wish to return home. 
  The Commission for the Affairs of Sudanese Working Abroad, 
Wednesday [11 May] urged the Sudanese living in Yemen who might 
wish to be evacuated, to proceed to a Sudanese vessel now 
anchored at the north Yemeni al-Hudaydah port on the Red Sea. 
The commission said in a statement issued in Khartoum that the 
national airline, Sudanair, would arrange a flight to the north 
Yemeni capital, Sanaa, on 14 May to evacuate Sudanese. It urged 
those wishing to take the flight back home to register their 
names at the Embassy of Sudan in Sanaa. 
  No arrangements were announced for the evacuation of 
Sudanese 
from Aden, capital of south Yemen. The commission said it had 
set up a task force comprising concerned government bodies and 
opened an operations room to accomplish the job. 
  Tens of thousands of Sudanese nationals were employed in the 
two Yemens as doctors, teachers, workers and journalists, among 
other professions. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

