<H3> <TI>   Knesset Endorses Rabin Speech After Opposition Walkout </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Knesset Endorses Rabin Speech After Opposition Walkout </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1105183194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1800 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1105183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] All opposition Knesset members [MK's] left the 
plenum prior to the vote held in conclusion of the debate at 
which Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin presented the Gaza and 
Jericho agreements. In the opposition's absence, the prime 
minister's speech was endorsed by a majority of 52 versus zero 
opponents. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht notes that some 
opposition MK's, including Dan Meridor, Beni Begin, Yitzhaq 
Shamir, and David Levi, were sharply opposed to abandoning the 
plenum. They maintained that the step is a violation of 
parliamentary rules. 
  Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, who closed the debate, said 
that in the Likud era, 120,000 Palestinians were locked up in 
prisons, which were schools for nationalism and the reason for 
the emergence of a Palestinian nation and a Palestinian entity 
in Gaza. 

</TEXT>

