<H3> <TI>   No MK Parliamentary Immunity in Autonomy Areas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No MK Parliamentary Immunity in Autonomy Areas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205101694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 12 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1205101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Attorney General Mikha'el Ben-Ya'ir has ruled that 
after the transfer of powers to the Palestinian authority in 
Gaza and Jericho, Knesset members [MK] will no longer enjoy 
parliamentary immunity and special privileges in those areas. 
In all other areas of Judaea, Samaria, and Gaza MK's enjoy 
special privileges stemming from their position, and the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] authorities must respect them. 
  Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports the attorney general 
emphasized that in the event of a clash between security needs 
in the area and the right of an MK to freedom of movement, the 
security needs will prevail. Mikha'el Ben-Ya'ir was addressing 
the Knesset House Committee. 

</TEXT>

