<H4>    Committee Resumes Meetings </H4>

<F P=102> JN1105160994 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Jordanian-Palestinian Economic Committee 
resumed its meetings at the Prime Ministry today. The Jordanian 
side was led by Dr. Jawad al-'Anani, minister of state for 
cabinet affairs and minister of information. The Palestinian 
side was led by Ahmad Quray', head of the PLO Economic 
Department. 
  The committee began its meetings yesterday. The agenda 
includes discussing many economic issues, such as banks, 
currency, trade exchanges, customs, and other issues. 

