<H3> <TI>   Economic Committee Meetings With PLO Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economic Committee Meetings With PLO Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    PLO's Quray Comments on Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105210394 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ahmad Quray', alias Abu-'Ala, director of the PLO's 
economic affairs and planning department, has said that 
Jordanian and Palestinian delegations held intensive economic 
talks yesterday. The talks focused deeply and comprehensively on 
all the details of every aspect of Jordanian-Palestinian 
economic relations and the Palestinian-Israeli economic 
agreement, recently signed in Paris. 
  In a statement after the talks, which lasted for five hours, 
Brother Abu-'Ala said that it was stressed that the 
Jordanian-Palestinian economic agreement signed in Amman early 
this year is the basis for the Jordanian-Palestinian 
relationship. He pointed out that discussions on bilateral 
issues are still under way and will be resumed today. 
  Brother Abu-'Ala said that no changes will be made to the 
bases and principles of the Jordanian-Palestinian economic 
agreement. Discussions of the issues of banks, trade, currency, 
and customs will be continued. 

</TEXT>

