<H3> <TI>   Egypt's Sidqi Urges Response to PLO-Israel Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Egypt's Sidqi Urges Response to PLO-Israel Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205122294 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 9 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1205122294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AL-MAJD has learned that Egyptian Prime Minister Dr. 
'Atif Sidqi has urged the Jordanian Government to respond 
positively to the requirements of the Palestinian-Israeli 
agreement, both the political part which was signed in Cairo, 
and the economic part which was recently signed in Paris. 
  Dr. Sidqi, who led the Egyptian side to the meetings of the 
Joint Jordanian-Egyptian Higher Committee, has linked the 
reactivation of Egyptian-Jordanian economic cooperation with 
Jordan's response to the strategic U.S. policies, "which Egypt 
is concerned about implementing in the field of comprehensive 
development in the region," as Sidqi put it, and which Egypt 
cannot disregard. 
  He said that his visit to Amman reflects Egypt's concern 
about reactivating Jordan's role in the economic plan set for 
the region, which will begin in the occupied territories, in 
which Jordan is a key player, and which will eventually lead to 
the creation of a Middle East economic entity, and later a 
political entity. 

</TEXT>

