<H4>    Press Urged To Aid Probe </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105181794 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1630 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The first press festival ended this afternoon 
with a speech by President Hashemi-Rafsanjani and the 
presentation of prizes to the outstanding press in the country. 
  In his speech, the president considered the progress of the 
country's press to be towards perfection and described the press 
festival as a necessity for this stage in the era of the 
reconstruction of the country. 
  Mr. Hashemi-Rafsanjani stressed the need for press freedom 
in 
the country and added: Press freedom in Iran is at a very high 
level. Even those in the press who do not have a friendly 
approach enjoy the same freedom. 
  The president stressed the need for the press to come to the 
aid of the government when necessary and added: When the 
British Government embarked on a hue and cry against us in the 
current month [Iranian month beginning 21 April] as a preemptive 
action after a bugging device was discovered at the Iranian 
Embassy, the press did not show any perceptiveness [hassasiyyat 
neshan-nadadand]. Professionals realize the press should come to 
the aid of the government at such times. [passage omitted] 

