<H3> <TI>   President Accuses UK of Bugging London Embassy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Accuses UK of Bugging London Embassy </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    British Envoy Summoned </H4>

<F P=102> LD1205104294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1205104294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with the deputy foreign minister for 
European and American affairs, a few minutes ago, our 
correspondent asked him to give further details about the 
espionage action by British agents against Iran. 
  During the interview, Mr. Va'ezi gave a detailed description 
of the spying equipment installed at the Iranian Embassy in 
London and how it was discovered, He also described the Foreign 
Ministry's actions on the matter. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified correspondent] Mr. Va'ezi, 
if 
possible please give our dear listeners more details on the 
discovery of the British Government eavesdropping device at the 
Iranian Embassy in London. 
  [Va'ezi] In the name of God, the compassionate, the 
merciful. 
About two weeks ago, when tearing down a wall in the new Iranian 
Embassy building in London, we discovered a bug installed and 
realized that a bug had been placed there. With the discovery 
of the bug, because of intelligence and operational 
considerations, and in order to conduct further investigation, 
we did not disclose the matter and continued our investigations 
until it was made public yesterday. 
  The bug weighs about half a kilogram. A battery has been 
fitted inside it. It has a number of parts and in effect acts 
as a transmitter. In any case, this is the latest thing we can 
announce in connection with the bug. 
  [Correspondent] Please tell us what measures the Iranian 
Foreign Ministry has so far taken in response to this action of 
the British Government? 
  [Va'ezi] After our investigation at the embassy was 
concluded 
the British Embassy's charge d'affaires in Tehran was summoned 
today by the director general for Western Europe. A strong 
protest was made against this action of the British Government. 
We asked them to give us more explanations as quickly as 
possible. In any case, future explanations by the British 
Government will determine the next steps. 
  Basically, we consider this and the British Government's 
behavior toward us as a weak point in our relations and in line 
with Britain's overall policy on Iran. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you very much. 
  [Va'ezi] Thank you. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

