<H3> <TI>   King Fahd Receives Phone Call From Yemeni President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Fahd Receives Phone Call From Yemeni President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105211294 Riyadh SPA in English 1941 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105211294 </F>
<F P=104>  Riyadh SPA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riyadh, May 11, SPA -- Custodian of the two holy 
mosques King Fahd Bin-'Abd-al-'Aziz received a telephone call 
from Yemeni President Lt. General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih on 
Tuesday [10 May]. 
  They reviewed bilateral relations and the current 
developments in Yemen, security in the Gulf region and the 
mutual interests of the kingdom and the Republic of Yemen. 
  On Wednesday, visiting Yemeni Chairman of the House of 
Deputies Sheikh 'Abdullah bin Husayn al-Ahmar and Planning and 
Development Minister Dr. 'Abd-al-Karim al-Iryani conveyed a 
message to King Fahd from Lt. General Salih during their 
audience with the monarch at al- Yamama Palace here. 
  The audience was attended by Second Deputy Premier, Minister 
of Defence and Aviation and Inspector General Prince Sultan 
Bin-'Abd- al-'Aziz, the special adviser to the monarch Ibrahim 
al-Anqari and the Yemeni ambassador to the kingdom Ghalib 'Ali 
Jameel [name as received]. 
  Sheikh al-Ahmar and Dr. al-Iryani arrived here last night 
and 
were greeted at the airport by al-Anqari and Jameel. 

</TEXT>

