<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> United Arab Emirates </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemeni Minister Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yemeni Minister Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1205074294 Manama WAKH in Arabic 0550 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1205074294 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Abu Dhabi, 11 May (WAKH)--Yemeni Minister of Oil and 
Mineral Resources Salih Abu-Bakr Bin-Husaynun has announced that 
his visit to the United Arab Emirates [UAE] comes within a tour 
that will also take him to Egypt and Syria. In a statement to 
the Emirates News Agency, WAM, Bin-Husaynun said that during the 
visit he will convey a message from Yemeni Vice President 'Ali 
Salim al- Bid to His Highness UAE President Shaykh Zayid 
Bin-Sultan Al Nuhayyan. 
  The Yemeni minister denied that the ongoing conflict in 
Yemen 
is over oil, noting that oil was discovered in northern and 
southern Yemen before the unity and that there are big oil 
reserves in the North and South. He added that oil production 
projects are proceeding normally in the northern and southern 
oil fields. However, he said, exploration and drilling stopped 
at the beginning of the war operations. 
  Asked if it is possible to continue talks about merger in 
light of the ongoing war between the North and South, the Yemeni 
minister said that Aden is now speaking about unity and the 
accord document [signed in Amman]. He said: What is required 
is to implement the document in letter and spirit, otherwise 
nothing else will be accepted by the Yemeni people. 
  Asked about Sanaa's call for an immediate cease-fire 
provided 
that Aden recognizes legitimacy, the Yemeni oil and mineral 
resources minister said: Aden supports the cease-fire. It has 
responded to cease-fire calls by some Arab brothers out of its 
concern to stop Yemeni bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-59316 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes092_j_94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-092 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dawn Scud Attack Launched 11 May; More Than 23 Killed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dawn Scud Attack Launched 11 May; More Than 23 Killed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105145094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1407 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a treacherous and cowardly act that can be 
committed only by hysterical people who sense that their demise 
is inevitable and who face the gloomy fate that awaits every 
murderer, the gang of apostasy and secession in the Yemeni 
Socialist Party [YSP] Command has fired its destructive 
long-range Scud missiles against civilian installations and 
residential quarters in Sanaa and other Yemeni cities in the 
northern and western governorates. A missile fell on a 
residential quarter in Sanaa at dawn today, martyring more than 
23 citizens, completely demolishing four houses, and damaging 
others. The bodies of a newly-wed couple, still in the first 
week of their marriage, were removed from under the rubble. 
  The masses that arrived on the scene condemned this criminal 
act that targets the lives of citizens -- women, children, and 
the elderly -- and denounced these vindictive actions carried 
out by the seccessionist clique in the YSP. These show the 
rancor this clique harbors toward the sons of our people. 
  Another missile fell on al-Rahidah Hospital the day before 
yesterday, killing many patients. 
  All these criminal acts are part of the attempt to undermine 
our people. However, these acts will only make our people more 
committed to unity and more insistent on defending it and 
protecting Constitutional legitimacy, and more determined to rid 
themselves of killers and murderers who have no qualms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

