<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Military Source' Issues Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Military Source' Issues Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105181794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1720 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A military source today made the following statement: 
  In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. In 
continuation of their treacherous, criminal acts and in a 
hysterical act that can be carried out only by cowardly people 
who bear a grudge against the people and the homeland, the gang 
of rebellion and secession after midnight yesterday fired two 
long-range Scud missiles against civilian installations and 
residential quarters in the Governorate of Sanaa. 
  One of the missiles fell in the early hours today on one of 
the populated quarters in the city of Sanaa. Its explosion 
destroyed four houses. As a result, 23 people were martyred and 
30 others sustained various injuries. Seven other houses were 
destroyed. An entire family was martyred in this criminal, 
sinful incident. 
  The source condemned this cowardly act that targeted the 
life 
of citizens and innocent women and children. 
  The source said these acts of revenge, practiced by the 
secessionist clique in the [Yemeni] Socialist Party, reflect the 
extent of the inveterate grudge in the hearts of this clique 
against the sons of our people. These acts reflect the bitter 
defeat tasted by this clique. 
  The source said these criminal acts will only increase our 
people's cohesion and resolve to score a great success for unity 
and Constitutional legitimacy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

