<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Southern Jets Engage Northern Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Southern Jets Engage Northern Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1105152494 Paris AFP in English 1445 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1105152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Aden, Yemen, May 11 (AFP)--Southern Yemeni jets 
and artillery pounded rival northern forces Wednesday east of 
the strategic southern port city of Aden, a correspondent 
reported. 
  The heaviest fire was concentrated on the Zinjibar area, 
about 60 kilometres (36 miles) east of Aden, as well as Ja'ar 
and Bakis, where the northern al-'Amaliqah brigade is based. 
  Meanwhile, northern forces were also trying to open up a new 
front in the Bab al-Mandeb area, about 400 kilometres (248 
miles) west of Aden, said Culture Minister Jarallah 'Umar, a 
southerner. 
  An AFP correspondent reported that southern planes made 
numerous sorties over Aden. The southern air force is 
considered stronger than that of the north. [passage omitted] 
  Some 12,000 northern troops are stationed in Abyan province, 
east of Aden, analysts say. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

