<H3> <TI>   South, North Claim Military Successes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South, North Claim Military Successes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205101694 Paris AFP in English 0935 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1205101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Aden, Yemen, May 12 (AFP) -- Southern forces in 
Yemen's civil war shot down three northern warplanes and sank a 
warship west of the vital port city of Aden, a southern 
commander announced Thursday. 
  Colonel 'Ali Qasim Talib, the sacked Yemeni navy chief, told 
the Aden daily 14 UKTUBAR the northern targets were hit late 
Wednesday in the Haraz region, near the strategic Bab el-Mandeb 
Straits on the Red Sea. 
  Earlier the northern forces loyal to President 'Ali 
'Abdallah 
Salih claimed they had captured a southern mechanised brigade 
based at Haraz. 
  A northern military communique quoted by the official news 
agency SABA' said northern forces had captured all the tanks and 
artillery of the southern 25th mechanised brigade, and many of 
the brigade's 1,200 soldiers had surrendered. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

