<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-'Attas Says Dismissal `Null,' `Void' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-'Attas Says Dismissal `Null,' `Void' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1105103094 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 11 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1105103094 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Al-'Attas Tells AL-HAYAH: My </F>
Dismissal Illegal, All My Contacts Aimed at Halting War"] 
  [Excerpt] London, AL-HAYAH -- Prime Minister Haydar 
Abu-Bakr al-'Attas has told AL-HAYAH that the "decision to 
dismiss me is null and void and illegal." Al-'Attas was 
answering a question put to him by AL-HAYAH, which contacted him 
in the hospital where he is receiving medical treatment in the 
United States. He said: "All the contacts I have made in the 
United States are aimed at halting the war. The situation which 
has emerged is saddening and we have warned of it a lot in the 
past. It is easy to launch a war, but it is difficult to end 
it." Asked about the way out, he said: "The way out is to halt 
the war and return to dialogue in order to implement the Pledge 
and Accord Document. We have agreed in the past that war is not 
the way to settle disputes, because it will bring nothing but 
destruction and tragedies for our people." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

