<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sanaa Said To Reject PLO Mediation; Fatah Aide Cited </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanaa Said To Reject PLO Mediation; Fatah Aide Cited </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1105143794 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 11 May 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PM1105143794 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Sanaa Rejects 'Arafat's Mediation"] </F>
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Sanaa has rejected an 
offer of mediation made two days ago by the Palestinian 
leadership in an endeavor to stop the war in Yemen. Vice 
President 'Ali Salim al-Bid welcomed the Palestinian offer of 
mediation, which would have been carried out by Fatah Central 
Committee Member 'Abbas Zaki, who enjoys excellent relations 
with the Yemenis, especially in south Yemen where he worked as 
representative of the Palestinian revolution in Aden several 
years ago. 
  That is what Zaki himself said. He told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT 
that he would have left for Yemen had President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih accepted the mediation, but the Yemeni president's 
announcement three days ago rejecting any Arab or foreign 
mediation, on the grounds that what was happening in Yemen was 
an internal affair, prevented him from carrying out the mission 
entrusted to him by Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat. 

</TEXT>

