Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   YSP Official Says Civil War To Affect Generations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    YSP Official Says Civil War To Affect Generations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1105210894 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1105210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. Yasin Sa'id Nu'man, the chairman of the board of 
the secretariat of the Central Committee of the Yemeni Socialist 
Party [YSP], emphasized that those who ran away from 
implementing the pledge and accord document about which they 
used to talk a big mouth talk are the ones who plunged Yemen 
into civil infighting and who set plans for a brutal crime, the 
effect of which will not end for generations to come. 
  He clarified in an interview with the Middle East satellite 
television channel, MBC, that the war imposed on the Yemeni 
people has levelled the gunpowder, the bullets, and the shells 
to the heart of the unity and that the unity has been stabbed in 
the back. Pointing to those who committed this brutal crime, he 
said that this brutal crime did not only lead to the killing of 
the citizens in the peaceful villages and cities but it also 
directed a stab against the Yemeni people and to its history and 
future. He said: In this critical situation I call upon ... if 
we want to preserve something for the future, it is in the 
interests of Yemen that people are pledged to a logic rather 
than the logic of war. [sentence as heard] As for some, to put 
the invasion or the manipulation is the impossible which cannot 
be done. [sentence as heard] Dr. Yasin Sa'id Nu'man reiterated 
that he that received reports from the war- mongers must know 
that they are [word indistinct]. He expressed satisfaction 
about the good intermediation efforts and said in this 
connection: Those who reject these intermediation under the 
illusion of achieving a military victory must wake up from their 
illusions, which I am afraid will hit them in their strongholds. 
  [Al-Jundi] What is the purpose of your visit to Riyadh? 
  [Al-Iryani] To discuss bilateral ties and explain the 
situation in Yemen. 
  [Al-Jundi] Reports say that you personally were behind the 
failure of the meeting between President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih 
and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid in Salalah in Oman. You 
reportedly said that the southerners offered proposals that 
contradict Yemeni unity. 
  [Al-Iryani] Yes. This remains my opinion. I believe in it. 
  [Al-Jundi] Can we say that President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
as 
chairman of the Presidential Council, can issue a cease-fire 
order to protect Yemeni unity and, above all, Yemeni blood? 
  [Al-Iryani] If the Armed Forces obey the authority of the 
state and the orders of the supreme commander of the Armed 
Forces, then I am sure he will. 
  [Al-Jundi] The Presidential Council dismissed Prime Minister 
Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas and the defense minister, while the 
House of Representatives dismissed Presidential Council Vice 
Chairman 'Ali Salim al-Bid. Al-'Attas told the Voice of the 
Arabs that the decisions were illegitimate and that the House of 
Representatives and the Presidential Council had no right to 
carry out such dismissals. 
  [Al-Iryani] Concerning the prime minister, the defense 
minister, and the oil minister, they were dismissed on the basis 
of a clear constitutional provision, namely, Article 111. The 
House of Representatives did not withdraw confidence from 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid, but from those who support secession and work 
against Yemeni unity. 
  [Al-Jundi] Through your current contacts, is there a glimmer 
of hope for a settlement and calm in Yemen or will the war 
continue? 
  [Al-Iryani] You cannot lose hope. I believe the fighting 
will not continue long, but that sense and reason will prevail. 
  [Al-Jundi] Thank you. 
  [Al-Iryani] You are welcome. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

