<H3> <TI>   Paper Urges People To Fight `Sick' Family </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Paper Urges People To Fight `Sick' Family </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1105214494 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in English 
1600 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1105214494 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the press review] </F>
  [Text] The current aggression by the al-Ahmar gang on the 
armed forces of unity and democracy has been dealt with by the 
local newspapers. SAWT AL-UMMAL newspaper in its issue affirmed 
that the criminal acts by the al-Ahmar military family 
culminated with the ignition of the civil war and the 
inter-Yemen war. 
  The newspaper indicated that the ugliest images of envy had 
become evident in the hundreds of dead and thousands of injured. 
The newspaper said in this connection: We do not find words to 
express this criminal tragedy experienced by our Yemeni people 
today as the result of a sick president and a family which is 
mainly concerned to preserve its interests and continues to 
[word indistinct] the people's fortunes and wealth. The 
newspaper quoted the proverb which says: He who digs a hole for 
his brother falls in. The newspaper went on to say that the 
al-Ahmar ruling family has declared confrontation between it and 
the people. The people must therefore join their armed forces 
in order to decide the match and normalize the matter by 
restoring the authority to the people so that the people and 
their armed forces could stand against this crime, which is 
commanded by 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 'Ali Muhsin al- Ahmar and his 
brother, Muhammad 'Abdallah Salih and other highwaymen. SAWT 
AL-UMMAL said that the conspiracy against the people became 
complete with the ruling family's decision to declare a state of 
emergency. By this the family unmasked its ugly face, which is 
hostile to democracy, unity, and civil and human rights. 

</TEXT>

