<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Company Fixes Fuel Prices, Warns Against Violations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Company Fixes Fuel Prices, Warns Against Violations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1105105494 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
0907 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1105105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Yemeni Oil Company, department of gas stations, 
warns the gas station owners in all parts of the Republic of 
Yemen that they should strictly abide by the prices of the oil 
byproducts as they have always been and as follows: 
  One liter of gasoline: six rials 
  One liter of diesel oil: three rials. 
  One liter of kerosene: three rials. 
  Whoever violates this list will have his license withdrawn 
and the gas station will be closed. Strict legal measures will 
also be taken against him. 
  The Company will launch a monitoring campaign on all 
stations 
in coordination with the security authorities to maintain the 
prices. The Company appeals to the brother citizens to cooperate 
and abide by the official price list and to immediately report 
any violations so that strict measures can be taken against the 
violators. All are requested to abide by these prices and 
cooperate. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

