<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Radio Report on Bhutto, Israeli President Meeting Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Radio Report on Bhutto, Israeli President Meeting Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1205103194 Islamabad THE MUSLIM in English 12 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BK1205103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad THE MUSLIM </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Islamabad, May 11 -- A Foreign Office spokesman 
while talking to THE MUSLIM Wednesday [11 May] night 
categorically denied that Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto held a 
meeting with Israeli President Weizman in South Africa. 
  Asked to comment on Israeli Radio's Persian language news 
about Benazir-Weizman meeting on May 10, the spokesman described 
it a fabrication. He said that it was part of the 
disinformation campaign of Israeli Radio to malign Pakistan by 
spreading lies. He said that in the past also, Israeli Radio 
had been spreading false news about such contacts. 
  Israeli Radio in its Persian language news broadcast at 7 pm 
on May 10, had stated that Israeli President Weizman held a 
meeting with Pakistan Prime Minister Ms Bhutto in South Africa. 
It said the experts were of the view that this unprecedented 
meeting was an indication that Pakistan was moving towards 
establishment of full-fledged diplomatic relations with Israel. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

