Daily Report 
<DATE1>  8 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto Reiterates Support for `Just' Kashmiri `Struggle' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bhutto Reiterates Support for `Just' Kashmiri `Struggle' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0805124694 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 
1100 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0805124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister, Ms. Benazir Bhutto, has said 
that Pakistan would continue to extend its full support to the 
Kashmiri people in their just struggle against the Indian 
occupation forces so that they can achieve their right of 
self-determination according to the UN resolution. 
  Speaking at the installation ceremony of the new colonel 
commandant of Baloch Regiment, she reiterated that Pakistan will 
not budge an inch from its principled stand on Kashmir. The 
prime minister said no nation can be subjugated for long with 
bullets and swords. The day will come when the Kashmiris will 
be able to achieve their rights, she said. 
  The prime minister said Pakistan has no aggressive designs 
against any country. It believes in peaceful coexistence. It 
desires to have good neighborly relations with all on the basis 
of equality, but it cannot compromise on its principle just for 
the sake of friendship. Pakistan cannot allow anyone to cast an 
evil eye on its independence and solidarity. The prime minister 
said that the government is fully conscious of the needs of its 
armed forces and is taking all steps to meet their requirements. 
It is doing its best to keep the armed forces fully equipped to 
effectively defend the country to frustrate any aggression. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

